(window.webpackJsonp=window.webpackJsonp||[]).push([[45],{303:function(module,exports){module.exports={compilerOutput:[],storyContent:{inkVersion:19,root:[[{"->t->":"chapter_16_sound"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_mother_died_yesterday_or_today"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_hollow_women"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_noir_prophetess_of_doom"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_follow_the_bouncing_ball"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_silent_grief_mothers_heart"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_interception_and_secret_interdiction"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_behold_the_chariot"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_lystra_symphorians_lament"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_16_manning_womanning_and_catting_the_barricades"},"ev","str","^","/str","/ev",{"->":"done"},["done",{"#f":5,"#n":"g-0"}],null],"done",{chapter_16_sound:['^<play-sound group="music" name="fast-approaching-mayhem" />',"\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_mother_died_yesterday_or_today:["^<p>","\n","^Mother takes my hand and holds it tight.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Now she slips from my grasp.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Now she is before me, walking towards the field of blazing crosses.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Each of the crucified lions look fake now, in the death-dance of light and forms, like empty men stuffed with straw, scarecrows dancing in the wind. The smoke is thickening. The screams are everywhere and it has become impossible to tell the glad from the dying.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Mother is lapsing into shadow, becoming imperceptible. Everything around her seems to narrow; everything within her seems kaleidoscopic, desaturated.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Shape without form, form without motion, shade without color, paralysis unchained and sharpened to a point.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Gesture without movement, feeling without presence, traveling through the parallax view of my gaze, instant by paradoxical instant.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Now she is, without being. A perpetual star, collapsing, the rose of the twilight sun unfurling, emptiness pouring out of her as invisible radiation.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^This is the only rule of the universe: that which is swallowed will come up as both itself and other.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Someone else has glimpsed her. Perhaps another of the Group. It is impossible to tell what is me, what is the others, what is the mob, what is the stink of death and lack of oxygen.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Now many have seen her, but in this most final of meeting places, gathered on the field of the city below the hill, all across the deathland, no one has words any longer.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^There are attempts, halting and intense, ululations and strangled cries, the outpouring of the language of tongues. But this is just fumbling, and no one speaks a word until suddenly a sharp voice cries out.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_hollow_women:["^<p>","\n",'^"Mother \u2014 she\'s dead!"',"\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^I can hear her now, though.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^She is in my mind. Everything else is quiet.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n",'^"Go, darling. Take the Group. Go to the chariot. I am with you every step of the way. Where you see a canyon big enough only for your quinternity, five by one through the chasm of death, billions ride atop your back."',"\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death:[["^<p>","\n","^We're at least a klick out from the nearest gate, mostly southerly. Any way, north, northeast, or northwest, could get us back to Carcassonne.","\n","^</p>","\n",["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death.0.6.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0",flg:18},{s:["^We return due north.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death.0.7.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1",flg:18},{s:["^We take a hook around to the northeast.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death.0.8.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-2",flg:18},{s:["^We travel back to Carcassonne by northwest.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.6.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^<p>","\n","^Others are following before us, having left early, never joined, or rushing, in panic and terror, back to their only sensible home.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Zion and Joppa are both filled with frightened renunciants. The word of Mother's demise, or her bodily death, spreads faster than men. Shouts are rising, a crush forming.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Instead we make our way through piles of garbage, feces, rats, roaches, and into the soiled expanses of the Waste Gate.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death.0.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.7.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^<p>","\n","^The Golden Gate is already burning by the time we return. Lions Gate is the most fortified, machine-gunners, automatic grenade launchers, MANPADs, the works. We'd just as easily end up mowed down by our own Perfect lieutenants.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^And so we embark on the longest way, to Herod's Gate, rusted and pre-rev, never fixed since our arrival. It takes several minutes for the lone guard to figure out how the door console works.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death.0.c-2.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.8.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^<p>","\n","^Word comes over the radio from one of the captains who stayed at base. Joppa's already been closed, nuclear-strength fire doors dropped. No one even has a key, and nothing in the entire world, not even a bomb, is going to lift that gate off its hinges.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Novo Gate is likely to be the safest, given we're already on the way. It's also, well, very fresh and strong construction. So if we're going to get the big one dropped on us this time, well, that's the tornado shelter of note, there's not get a bigger doorframe than that.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Novo is also on the other side of all the Antediluvian/Commando vectors. They can send fireforces, envelop us vertically, but they're likely still determining cause and process.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^We take the new road to the Novo Gate, haunted the whole way by the growing buzz of distant aircraft, sobs floating on the wind, bird calls and gusting trees which sound like our departed parents.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":["^<p>","\n","^Every technology of language and desire production will be brought to bear on erasing this void in the form constants of the Antediluvian State. The sign, broken and refashioned for the people, will be beaten back into a conquering sigil. The dream will die, and it will be replaced with the nightmare of history from which we can never wake.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Every transcendent crack in the firmament will be filled in, like mass graves topped with fresh soil, unguent spread across shallow wounds.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The alarms go off. The ones we only heard in sleep, in hypnopompic and psychopunk suicide practice. The gymnastics of dying are second nature to me by now.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n",'^"It is time to be transformed," the absent and motherly voice intones.',"\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n",'^"This is not a drill."',"\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Red lights and klaxons fight the word.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^There is the sound of a terrible explosion above, the <em>whuump</em> of fuel-air explosives. The smell of gasoline through failing air sanitizers admixed with the scent of death, smoke, and dewy morning. External pumps for air and water shut off and are replaced with the unearthly grinding of emergency systems.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Carcassonne is alive, its bones howling and its veins whispering. The spirit of 1244 is alive in every soul who yet breathes. The days of 1945 are speaking here, of 1968, 2001, and 2666. Every year has become one with the present, history compressed into a single day, the calendar flattened into a unitary moment in the shape of a diamond, ground into a wheel.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Falling sparks intermingle with pieces of vessels broken at the creation, palimpsests long since abraded. And, as Mother told it, someday, somehow, in the end, a gathering back to the Source. A final, dolorous stroke, struck at the last moment.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Now, within the flaming corpse of our dreams, I see no such message, no such home.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Only trillions of final seconds and nothing more.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The nightmare is nothing more than an assembly line of last moments, and its gears will not be stopped by every one of our corpses.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],chapter_16_noir_prophetess_of_doom:["^<p>","\n","^It is just here, in the final chiaroscuro frames of our terrible noir, that the pointed tip of that most secret of swords, falling at the speed of creation itself and utterly noiseless, reaches its final instant. The knife is poised, we are bound and gagged, and the bargain will not be reversed this time.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^There is still time, for those who were not deputized to act even beyond the veil of death as we know it, to embrace their fellow souls, or to brace their heads between their legs. Even bullets have a spacetime in which they hang, barely moving, like birds against the gale.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^We were here; we fought.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Standing on the new world's summit, the <em>har</em> of the old world, we launched our insolent challenges against all the constellations.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_follow_the_bouncing_ball:["^<p>","\n","^Now come the incendiaries with charred fingers and bleeding knives; now the world is to be delivered from the gangrene of perfection.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Or if hymns better guide them towards oblivion than secret history, here is one they may sing in plainsong, with only the accompaniment of all the futuristic instruments: great crowds agitated by death, gunfire and revolt, the nocturnal emissions of the Carcassonne arsenals and workshops beneath their killing electric moons, factories hung from the fake LED clouds by their thin industrial wisps, spiraling like sinister mobiles, the gliding flight of r-wings and f-wings whose engines speak in harmony with machine-gun fire.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<blockquote>","\n","^<p>","\n","^There is a Hand to turn the page,","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^There is a Voice to call the sage.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Till the Light that brought all the Towers low,","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Finds the last sick Perfect one.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Till the Lions sleep by every road,","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^All through our bleeding Zone.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^With a face for every death,","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^And a soul in every bone.","\n","^</p>","\n","^</blockquote>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_silent_grief_mothers_heart:["^<p>","\n","^How can I live without you, Mother? Must I? Am I to live at all?","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^At this she is totally silent.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_interception_and_secret_interdiction:["^<p>","\n","^The intercept channel is not. I can hear the Commando Aleph speaking their secret gospels, the language of death without vitality. I can hear the prayers of those who have accepted and the pleas of those who have not. All of this is in me, and of me. We arrive in the hangar as the lights begin to flicker and flutter.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The radio speaks of the destruction of a backup generator. They will be proceeding according to ancient plans, a technology of architecture which prefigured every single moment here. They will know exactly what is where and precisely what force will be necessary to gut us.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^But even by this clear and threatening predestination They are moving faster than belief.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Could it even be possible They were already here, waiting, false perfection drawing a trap all this time?  That they knew everything we were doing as or before we were doing it? Perhaps this whole war has been shadowplay, a prestidigitation, allowed solely to name our bodies as <em>casus belli</em> against our Word.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^So above as below, and no tunnel deep enough to ever escape Them.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_behold_the_chariot:["^<p>","\n","^The chariot is before us. The living machine, the creature which will carry us through a slipstream of faith and destiny to the chapel perilous, sits mute and closed. No entry ports or ladders are visible anywhere across its hundreds of meters of flank. Its only distinguishing mark besides oceans of limitless black is the icon of TAV, the emblem of the twilight sun.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^What is the meaning of this? Some final exercise or joke?","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_lystra_symphorians_lament:["^<p>","\n","^Lystra Symphorian speaks: \"We're gonna fucking die now. And then we're gonna roast. Game over. No more lives. You all know that, right? That girl in the audience, the one who said she was gonna have grandkids, we were gonna rot, and go someplace <em>way</em> worse than the piss ladder. Should've <em>god-damned</em> listened. Now I'm gonna die in a tunnel, fucking my rifle to death, just like I always knew I would.\"","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Lystra checks the mag for their rifle and charges the handle. They drop to a low ready pose behind a fallen pedestal and train their sight down the corridor.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^A pointless gesture in game theory, but just as brave as I knew to expect from Lystra. They were always going to go out, kicking, screaming, taking as many of those bastards with them as possible.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Lefteris looks over at Lystra for a minute, then turns towards the dark end of the tunnel, past the chariot.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<play-sound group="music" name="factory-parts-remix" />',"\n","^<p>","\n",'^"Stop. Listen. You hear that, right? Shut everything else out and focus."',"\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_manning_womanning_and_catting_the_barricades:['^<update-sound group="music" name="fast-approaching-mayhem" volume="0.2" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^There it is: a singing, harmony in discord with screams and klaxon howls, the banshee wail of mass love turning to ashes in the mouths of every lover at once.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^A squadron of twenty Perfect, holding rifles and molotovs, and a hundred datacats, panthers and jaguars against the dancing flames, wheeling in a four-barrelled antiaircraft gun. Soon their voices beat out the din like high tide does the seabirds. They salute and take position around us, moving rubble and carts, chairs and tables. All the proudest soldiers of the <em>passeporte jaune</em> assemble for one final stand against the lions. May the light of Source protect us in the den.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Now the cats are pushing us towards the sign, the one-eyed black and white longhair in the lead, flanked by a runt, holding what looks like some sort of antique semi-automatic. They drag, with their saintly and delicate knives, our ignorant hands atop the sigil.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The shadow sun burns against our hands, and we are taken into it. Like birth in reverse, dragged through something warm and tight, dark and enveloping, a mothering embrace from the cold and burning world.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_16_prayer_to_god:[["^<p>","\n","^Lystra remains three steps behind. They're staring at the artillery piece, watching the hammer fall and rise, their face strobing.","\n","^</p>","\n",["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_prayer_to_god.0.6.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0",flg:18},{s:["^I pray Lystra follows.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_prayer_to_god.0.7.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1",flg:18},{s:["^I call out for one of the datacats.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_prayer_to_god.0.8.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-2",flg:18},{s:["^I scream for Lystra at the top of my lungs.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_prayer_to_god.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.6.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^<p>","\n","^To the one true Mother below, here is my prayer.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Oh Mother, let Lystra hear the call of my mind.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^We, who would invade the house of the most high and holy, need the shade of your shadow.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^I say of you, Mother, you are fortress and spear, my creator, in whom I have placed faith beyond existence. Hear my prayer.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Mother, save Lystra from the commando's snare, and from the burning pestilence.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^They will be covered by fire and fur, and in watchful claws may they find refuge, shield, and sword.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^They will not be defeated by this last eve, nor struck down by the arrow of time,","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^nor the reaper who watches above all, nor the plague that destroys at midday.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^A billion may fall at our side, one million at your right hand, but we will win.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^You need only observe with eyes beyond body, and see the punishment of the architech of pain.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^We will be the raptors of the garden.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^No harm can befall us. No disaster may interdict our chariot. Not as we have you in our heart.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^With your name we will demand, of even the angels, amnesia for kneeling, obedience, and divine slander.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Or, if they refuse, we will show them how humans have learned to die, and they may practice the work.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Mother, lift us in your hands, past every star, beyond first light.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^We will tread upon the lion and the cobra; you will be the spikes in our feet when we trample the great lion and serpent.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Because you love us, Mother, so much you no longer need a face, we will call upon you, and you shall ever answer us.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^You have been with Lystra in dire troubles. Please deliver and honor them to us once more.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^With our last night we shall build the image of salvation.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^\u25fc","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Silence. Nothing. Just explosions and blood.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Lystra is barely visible against the advancing army. They begin to raise their rifle.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Then they hear, and return to the fold. A white cat and gray kitten, eyes gleaming in the fire, trundle behind.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_prayer_to_god.0.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.7.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^<p>","\n","^I make a soft catcall, barely audible even from my own lips atop artillery, small arms, volcanic screams. There should be no way anything can hear it.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The black and white one does, and so does the kitten who's always following her. They run over to Lystra, climb up their body like a tree. The big one hisses in Lystra's ear; the small one sinks her teeth into their neck, a wingless demon.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Now all three follow towards us, chiaroscuro and so outlined by fire they appear to be burning. We all take hands, and close our eyes.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_16_prayer_to_god.0.c-2.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.8.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","^<p>","\n",'^"<strong>Lystra</strong>."',"\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Words and sound seem to move through a slow medium. First there is the sound of a forty-mike-mike firing, almost soundlessly loud in a confined space. Like running a hand under scalding water. First the slightest burst of pain, then a molten, cold numbness.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Lystra turns to face me.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n",'^"<em>Get in the fucking chariot</em>!"',"\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^And so they do, along with two cats.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":["ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],yield:[["ev","str","^\u25fc","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0",flg:4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":["ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],done:[{"temp=":"out_var"},[["ev",{"VAR?":"out_var"},"/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["\n","ev",{"VAR?":"out_var"},"/ev",{"VAR=":"XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE",re:!0},{"->":"done.1.1"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^\u25fc","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0",flg:20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":['^<stop-sound group="music" name="fast-approaching-mayhem" />',"\n","done",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"global decl":["ev","str","^XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE","/str",{"VAR=":"DEBUG"},"str","^chapter-17","/str",{"VAR=":"XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE"},"/ev","end",null],"#f":1}],listDefs:{}},text:'VAR DEBUG = "XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE"\r\n\r\nVAR XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE = "chapter-17"\r\n\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_sound ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_mother_died_yesterday_or_today ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_hollow_women ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_noir_prophetess_of_doom ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_follow_the_bouncing_ball ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_silent_grief_mothers_heart ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_interception_and_secret_interdiction ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_behold_the_chariot ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_lystra_symphorians_lament ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_16_manning_womanning_and_catting_the_barricades ->\r\n\r\n-> done("")\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_sound ===\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="fast-approaching-mayhem" />\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_mother_died_yesterday_or_today ===\r\n<p>\r\nMother takes my hand and holds it tight.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow she slips from my grasp.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow she is before me, walking towards the field of blazing crosses.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEach of the crucified lions look fake now, in the death-dance of light and forms, like empty men stuffed with straw, scarecrows dancing in the wind. The smoke is thickening. The screams are everywhere and it has become impossible to tell the glad from the dying.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMother is lapsing into shadow, becoming imperceptible. Everything around her seems to narrow; everything within her seems kaleidoscopic, desaturated.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nShape without form, form without motion, shade without color, paralysis unchained and sharpened to a point.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nGesture without movement, feeling without presence, traveling through the parallax view of my gaze, instant by paradoxical instant.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow she is, without being. A perpetual star, collapsing, the rose of the twilight sun unfurling, emptiness pouring out of her as invisible radiation.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis is the only rule of the universe: that which is swallowed will come up as both itself and other.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSomeone else has glimpsed her. Perhaps another of the Group. It is impossible to tell what is me, what is the others, what is the mob, what is the stink of death and lack of oxygen.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow many have seen her, but in this most final of meeting places, gathered on the field of the city below the hill, all across the deathland, no one has words any longer.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere are attempts, halting and intense, ululations and strangled cries, the outpouring of the language of tongues. But this is just fumbling, and no one speaks a word until suddenly a sharp voice cries out.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_hollow_women ===\r\n<p>\r\n"Mother \u2014 she\'s dead!"\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI can hear her now, though.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nShe is in my mind. Everything else is quiet.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n"Go, darling. Take the Group. Go to the chariot. I am with you every step of the way. Where you see a canyon big enough only for your quinternity, five by one through the chasm of death, billions ride atop your back."\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_long_return_through_the_valley_of_death ====\r\n<p>\r\nWe\'re at least a klick out from the nearest gate, mostly southerly. Any way, north, northeast, or northwest, could get us back to Carcassonne.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n* We return due north.\r\n    <p>\r\n    Others are following before us, having left early, never joined, or rushing, in panic and terror, back to their only sensible home.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Zion and Joppa are both filled with frightened renunciants. The word of Mother\'s demise, or her bodily death, spreads faster than men. Shouts are rising, a crush forming.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    -> yield ->\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Instead we make our way through piles of garbage, feces, rats, roaches, and into the soiled expanses of the Waste Gate.\r\n    </p>\r\n* We take a hook around to the northeast.\r\n    <p>\r\n    The Golden Gate is already burning by the time we return. Lions Gate is the most fortified, machine-gunners, automatic grenade launchers, MANPADs, the works. We\'d just as easily end up mowed down by our own Perfect lieutenants.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    -> yield ->\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    And so we embark on the longest way, to Herod\'s Gate, rusted and pre-rev, never fixed since our arrival. It takes several minutes for the lone guard to figure out how the door console works.\r\n    </p>\r\n* We travel back to Carcassonne by northwest.\r\n    <p>\r\n    Word comes over the radio from one of the captains who stayed at base. Joppa\'s already been closed, nuclear-strength fire doors dropped. No one even has a key, and nothing in the entire world, not even a bomb, is going to lift that gate off its hinges.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Novo Gate is likely to be the safest, given we\'re already on the way. It\'s also, well, very fresh and strong construction. So if we\'re going to get the big one dropped on us this time, well, that\'s the tornado shelter of note, there\'s not get a bigger doorframe than that.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Novo is also on the other side of all the Antediluvian/Commando vectors. They can send fireforces, envelop us vertically, but they\'re likely still determining cause and process.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    -> yield ->\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    We take the new road to the Novo Gate, haunted the whole way by the growing buzz of distant aircraft, sobs floating on the wind, bird calls and gusting trees which sound like our departed parents.\r\n    </p>\r\n-\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEvery technology of language and desire production will be brought to bear on erasing this void in the form constants of the Antediluvian State. The sign, broken and refashioned for the people, will be beaten back into a conquering sigil. The dream will die, and it will be replaced with the nightmare of history from which we can never wake.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEvery transcendent crack in the firmament will be filled in, like mass graves topped with fresh soil, unguent spread across shallow wounds.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe alarms go off. The ones we only heard in sleep, in hypnopompic and psychopunk suicide practice. The gymnastics of dying are second nature to me by now.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n"It is time to be transformed," the absent and motherly voice intones.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n"This is not a drill."\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nRed lights and klaxons fight the word.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere is the sound of a terrible explosion above, the <em>whuump</em> of fuel-air explosives. The smell of gasoline through failing air sanitizers admixed with the scent of death, smoke, and dewy morning. External pumps for air and water shut off and are replaced with the unearthly grinding of emergency systems.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nCarcassonne is alive, its bones howling and its veins whispering. The spirit of 1244 is alive in every soul who yet breathes. The days of 1945 are speaking here, of 1968, 2001, and 2666. Every year has become one with the present, history compressed into a single day, the calendar flattened into a unitary moment in the shape of a diamond, ground into a wheel.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nFalling sparks intermingle with pieces of vessels broken at the creation, palimpsests long since abraded. And, as Mother told it, someday, somehow, in the end, a gathering back to the Source. A final, dolorous stroke, struck at the last moment.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow, within the flaming corpse of our dreams, I see no such message, no such home.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOnly trillions of final seconds and nothing more.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe nightmare is nothing more than an assembly line of last moments, and its gears will not be stopped by every one of our corpses.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_noir_prophetess_of_doom ===\r\n<p>\r\nIt is just here, in the final chiaroscuro frames of our terrible noir, that the pointed tip of that most secret of swords, falling at the speed of creation itself and utterly noiseless, reaches its final instant. The knife is poised, we are bound and gagged, and the bargain will not be reversed this time.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere is still time, for those who were not deputized to act even beyond the veil of death as we know it, to embrace their fellow souls, or to brace their heads between their legs. Even bullets have a spacetime in which they hang, barely moving, like birds against the gale.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWe were here; we fought.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nStanding on the new world\'s summit, the <em>har</em> of the old world, we launched our insolent challenges against all the constellations.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_follow_the_bouncing_ball ===\r\n<p>\r\nNow come the incendiaries with charred fingers and bleeding knives; now the world is to be delivered from the gangrene of perfection.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOr if hymns better guide them towards oblivion than secret history, here is one they may sing in plainsong, with only the accompaniment of all the futuristic instruments: great crowds agitated by death, gunfire and revolt, the nocturnal emissions of the Carcassonne arsenals and workshops beneath their killing electric moons, factories hung from the fake LED clouds by their thin industrial wisps, spiraling like sinister mobiles, the gliding flight of r-wings and f-wings whose engines speak in harmony with machine-gun fire.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\nThere is a Hand to turn the page,\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere is a Voice to call the sage.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTill the Light that brought all the Towers low,\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nFinds the last sick Perfect one.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTill the Lions sleep by every road,\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAll through our bleeding Zone.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWith a face for every death,\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAnd a soul in every bone.\r\n</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_silent_grief_mothers_heart ===\r\n<p>\r\nHow can I live without you, Mother? Must I? Am I to live at all?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAt this she is totally silent.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_interception_and_secret_interdiction ===\r\n<p>\r\nThe intercept channel is not. I can hear the Commando Aleph speaking their secret gospels, the language of death without vitality. I can hear the prayers of those who have accepted and the pleas of those who have not. All of this is in me, and of me. We arrive in the hangar as the lights begin to flicker and flutter.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe radio speaks of the destruction of a backup generator. They will be proceeding according to ancient plans, a technology of architecture which prefigured every single moment here. They will know exactly what is where and precisely what force will be necessary to gut us.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nBut even by this clear and threatening predestination They are moving faster than belief.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nCould it even be possible They were already here, waiting, false perfection drawing a trap all this time?  That they knew everything we were doing as or before we were doing it? Perhaps this whole war has been shadowplay, a prestidigitation, allowed solely to name our bodies as <em>casus belli</em> against our Word.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSo above as below, and no tunnel deep enough to ever escape Them.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_behold_the_chariot ===\r\n<p>\r\nThe chariot is before us. The living machine, the creature which will carry us through a slipstream of faith and destiny to the chapel perilous, sits mute and closed. No entry ports or ladders are visible anywhere across its hundreds of meters of flank. Its only distinguishing mark besides oceans of limitless black is the icon of TAV, the emblem of the twilight sun.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWhat is the meaning of this? Some final exercise or joke?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_lystra_symphorians_lament ===\r\n<p>\r\nLystra Symphorian speaks: "We\'re gonna fucking die now. And then we\'re gonna roast. Game over. No more lives. You all know that, right? That girl in the audience, the one who said she was gonna have grandkids, we were gonna rot, and go someplace <em>way</em> worse than the piss ladder. Should\'ve <em>god-damned</em> listened. Now I\'m gonna die in a tunnel, fucking my rifle to death, just like I always knew I would."\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLystra checks the mag for their rifle and charges the handle. They drop to a low ready pose behind a fallen pedestal and train their sight down the corridor.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA pointless gesture in game theory, but just as brave as I knew to expect from Lystra. They were always going to go out, kicking, screaming, taking as many of those bastards with them as possible.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLefteris looks over at Lystra for a minute, then turns towards the dark end of the tunnel, past the chariot.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="factory-parts-remix" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n"Stop. Listen. You hear that, right? Shut everything else out and focus."\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_manning_womanning_and_catting_the_barricades ===\r\n<update-sound group="music" name="fast-approaching-mayhem" volume="0.2" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere it is: a singing, harmony in discord with screams and klaxon howls, the banshee wail of mass love turning to ashes in the mouths of every lover at once.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA squadron of twenty Perfect, holding rifles and molotovs, and a hundred datacats, panthers and jaguars against the dancing flames, wheeling in a four-barrelled antiaircraft gun. Soon their voices beat out the din like high tide does the seabirds. They salute and take position around us, moving rubble and carts, chairs and tables. All the proudest soldiers of the <em>passeporte jaune</em> assemble for one final stand against the lions. May the light of Source protect us in the den.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow the cats are pushing us towards the sign, the one-eyed black and white longhair in the lead, flanked by a runt, holding what looks like some sort of antique semi-automatic. They drag, with their saintly and delicate knives, our ignorant hands atop the sigil.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe shadow sun burns against our hands, and we are taken into it. Like birth in reverse, dragged through something warm and tight, dark and enveloping, a mothering embrace from the cold and burning world.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_16_prayer_to_god ===\r\n<p>\r\nLystra remains three steps behind. They\'re staring at the artillery piece, watching the hammer fall and rise, their face strobing.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n* I pray Lystra follows.\r\n    <p>\r\n    To the one true Mother below, here is my prayer.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Oh Mother, let Lystra hear the call of my mind.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    We, who would invade the house of the most high and holy, need the shade of your shadow.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n    <p>\r\n    I say of you, Mother, you are fortress and spear, my creator, in whom I have placed faith beyond existence. Hear my prayer.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Mother, save Lystra from the commando\'s snare, and from the burning pestilence.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    They will be covered by fire and fur, and in watchful claws may they find refuge, shield, and sword.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    They will not be defeated by this last eve, nor struck down by the arrow of time,\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    nor the reaper who watches above all, nor the plague that destroys at midday.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    A billion may fall at our side, one million at your right hand, but we will win.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    You need only observe with eyes beyond body, and see the punishment of the architech of pain.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    We will be the raptors of the garden.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    No harm can befall us. No disaster may interdict our chariot. Not as we have you in our heart.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    With your name we will demand, of even the angels, amnesia for kneeling, obedience, and divine slander.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Or, if they refuse, we will show them how humans have learned to die, and they may practice the work.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Mother, lift us in your hands, past every star, beyond first light.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    We will tread upon the lion and the cobra; you will be the spikes in our feet when we trample the great lion and serpent.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Because you love us, Mother, so much you no longer need a face, we will call upon you, and you shall ever answer us.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    You have been with Lystra in dire troubles. Please deliver and honor them to us once more.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    With our last night we shall build the image of salvation.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    \u25fc\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    -> yield ->\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Silence. Nothing. Just explosions and blood.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Lystra is barely visible against the advancing army. They begin to raise their rifle.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Then they hear, and return to the fold. A white cat and gray kitten, eyes gleaming in the fire, trundle behind.\r\n    </p>\r\n* I call out for one of the datacats.\r\n    <p>\r\n    I make a soft catcall, barely audible even from my own lips atop artillery, small arms, volcanic screams. There should be no way anything can hear it.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    -> yield ->\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    The black and white one does, and so does the kitten who\'s always following her. They run over to Lystra, climb up their body like a tree. The big one hisses in Lystra\'s ear; the small one sinks her teeth into their neck, a wingless demon. \r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Now all three follow towards us, chiaroscuro and so outlined by fire they appear to be burning. We all take hands, and close our eyes.\r\n    </p>\r\n* I scream for Lystra at the top of my lungs.\r\n    <p>\r\n    "<strong>Lystra</strong>."\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Words and sound seem to move through a slow medium. First there is the sound of a forty-mike-mike firing, almost soundlessly loud in a confined space. Like running a hand under scalding water. First the slightest burst of pain, then a molten, cold numbness.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    -> yield ->\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    Lystra turns to face me.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    "<em>Get in the fucking chariot</em>!"\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n    And so they do, along with two cats.\r\n    </p>\r\n-\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== yield ===\r\n+ [\u25fc]\r\n-\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== done(out_var) ===\r\n{\r\n    - out_var:\r\n        ~ XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE = out_var\r\n}\r\n\r\n* [\u25fc]\r\n-\r\n\r\n// factory-parts-remix is ended in the next chapter.\r\n\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="fast-approaching-mayhem" />\r\n\r\n-> DONE'}}}]);